0.2 BEAM Light Chain Versus Antigen Affinity

These figures display the number and frequency of light chain clones (based on Clean_Clone_ID) detected in each ag6 expression bin. The data highlight whether certain light chain clones are enriched in high-binding cells.

0.3 BEAM Heavy Chain Versus Antigen Affinity

These figures provide a similar analysis for heavy chain clones. By comparing trends in heavy chain clonal frequency versus antigen binding, we can determine whether high-affinity cells preferentially express certain heavy chain clones.

0.4 Summary and Interpretation

Light chain clones showed a strong enrichment in bins with higher ag6 expression, suggesting that many high-affinity cells share common light chain features.

Heavy chain clones were distributed across a broader range of ag6 bins, but with noticeable peaks in mid-to-high expression levels, indicating partial enrichment.

These observations suggest that clonal expansion is associated with antigen affinity. Selection for clonesâespecially those with strong light chain contributionsâthat bind more strongly to antigen.
